NEW Packing Video!
#What’s it like to pack for a small ship, luxury cruise to Alaska? We filmed a “pack with me” onboard to share some tips and tricks! 
You’ll find the video linked in our profile! Here are a few things that may surprise you about our Seabourn Voyage: 
🌲There was only ONE formal night on our @seabourncruise - luxury doesn’t mean “stuffy” or overly dressy.
🌲We packed something we’ve never packed before to Alaska- waterproof pants! Find out why when you watch the packing video (link in bio).
🌲We packed for 10 nights to Alaska carry-on only! While this isn’t some thing that we encourage for every traveler, we *really* don’t like checking bags, so we made it happen. That meant doing lots of laundry on the ship. Fortunately, for us, self service laundry was complimentary on Seabourn and we LOVED that perk!

What are some of your best Alaska packing tips?

Welcome friends old and new!
It’s time for a “HELLO” and introduction to our new followers! 

I’m Sheri, a Texas-based Mama and Wife (25 years married this year!). We relocated to Texas for the amazing cost of living, proximity to a cruise port and excellent international airports. 

My family and I began creating travel tip videos for cruise travelers on YouTube in 2013. We started CruiseTipsTV to inspire cruise travelers to create their best travel experiences and we love to help you pack, plan and prepare for your cruise! 

A little about us! 

My husband is our full time video & podcast editor and our 14 year-old son is learning to write for our website and is my podcast sidekick now and then! When we’re not cruising, we’re working on our ranch, daydreaming about our next cruise, and planning awesome content for YOU!

We recently relocated to Texas and can’t wait to explore cruises from Galveston (share all your tips!!). 

With over 800 videos on our YouTube channel, you can find tips on just about anything cruise related - from packing for a cruise to Alaska to what it’s like to take a food tour in Sicily.

We’ve cruised “thirty something” times with 7 different cruise lines to Europe, Asia, Mexico, Alaska, The Caribbean, the Panama Canal and more. Our favorite cruise destinations are Japan and Europe, but we LOVE Alaska, the Caribbean and Mexican Riviera too! 

We’re surrounded by an amazing collection of travel-loving friends who have joined our community over the past 10 years. We welcome you and we invite you to join us on YouTube, our Podcast, and on AmazonLIVE. Check out the link in our bio to learn more about us, and how we serve our community! 

We love learning from YOU too, so if you have any topic suggestions for us, please share them! If you have questions, please ask. 

💗💙💗You’ll always find positivity and support here!

Konnichiwa!
We’re on Diamond Princess this week, sailing from Japan on a Summer Festivals voyage! 
Do you have any questions about this ship or cruising Japan with @princesscruises? Be sure to ask! 

We fell in LOVE with this region 5 years ago, and have been *so* ready to return. Japan is now reopened to tourism, and cruising is a wonderful way to see this area! 
Here’s why we love cruising from Japan:

🪷The seasons are DISTINCT- from Spring flowers to fall foliage and summer festivals- no cruise is the same. 
🪷Cruising is a relaxing way to travel in a region where the language, cuisine and transportation can be more complex.
🪷 Diamond Princess Cruises offers special regional touches that make the experience different and memorable. Think green tea ice cream, TWO cruise directors (check out our stories this week to learn why) a sushi restaurant and origami class! 
🪷You can cover thousands of miles and see many regions and prefectures in a short time, a great “taster” for traveling to Japan and Southeast Asia!

Follow along in our Instagram and Facebook stories and watch for a “pack with me” on YouTube later this week 💙
Questions about Diamond Princess are welcome! 

#Hosted #presstrip
Disclosure: you’ll see us using the hashtags #hosted and #presstrip this week. We are guests of Princess cruises on this voyage and all content and opinions are coming straight from our family! 

#diamondprincess #princesscruises #japancruise #japan #summerfestivaljapan #akita #aomori #yokohama #kochi #princesscruise

Our first port stop on our Diamond Princess summer festival cruise - Akita, Japan!
Akita is a mountainous northern prefecture on Honshu, Japan's main island. Many visit for the hot springs, especially those surrounding Lake Tazawa. This prefecture is also know for delicious Sake. 

During our visit, it was the last day of the The Kanto Matsuri - aka the pole lantern festival - held each year from August 3rd to 6th. Performers balance kanto, a long bamboo pole with paper lanterns attached. Aong with the Aomori Nebuta Festival and Sendai Tanabata festival, makes up the three great festivals of the Tohoku Region.
The Kanto pole sizes go up to 12 meters, and support up to 46 paper lanterns with real candles. These are hoisted up high in performance to the sound of drums, flutes, as people chant "Dokkoisho, dokkoisho."
TIP: if you’re planning a summer festival visit to Japan- the weather is warm and humid! Pack cool clothing, hydrate and plan accordingly! It was 94 degrees on our visit and an air conditioned bus never felt better! 

#diamondprincess #princesscruises #akitajapan #japan #kantofestival

5 REASONS we love cruising Japan and Southeast Asia!
1️⃣ DISTINCT seasons- spring flowers, summer festivals and fall blooms! All so diffent from one another!
2️⃣ Cruising is comfortable and STRESS- free! From @princesscruises Medallion class comforts to port hopping without the worry of transportation or hotel changes, cruising is RELAXING! 

3️⃣ Culture! Japan offers a clean, safe and VIBRANT array of activities and ways to see the world through a new lens!

4️⃣ Seeing many cities in a short time- you’ll wake up in a new location every day! No packing/unpacking.
 5️⃣ FRIENDLY locals! be sure to head to the open decks as it cruise IN or OUT of each Japanese port as the locals will likely come to greet you with song, music and the most WARM, inviting spirit!

Welcome to our new followers! We’re so glad you’re here! 

A little about us here at CruiseTipsTV...

I’m Sheri, a Texas-based Mama and Wife. I fell in love with cruise travel when my Mom took me on a Carnival cruise for my high school graduation in 1991. I was HOOKED on the idea of being at sea. Life got busy, and I didn’t cruise again until 2003. After being married for 5 years, I told my husband “We’ve just gotta try this cruise thing together”. To my surprise, he was even more enamored with cruise travel than I was, and we never looked back. We had our (one and only) son in 2008, and he spent his first birthday on a Holland America cruise with extended family.

After filming our family travel memories for a few years, we had a feeling that we wanted to share our passion for cruise travel, so, we jumped in headfirst and began creating tip videos for cruise travelers on YouTube in 2013. We started with cruise packing videos (still my favorite). Over the years, we added many types of videos (vlogs, ship tours, and cruise info), to help people with their cruise questions and inspire them to create their best travel experiences. 

When we’re not cruising, we’re home riding ATVs, cooking, and taking care of our farm. 

We’ve expanded to many different platforms over the past 10 years, and the link in our bio will take you to our podcast, website, YouTube and MORE! 

P.S. -  You’ll *always* find positivity and support here!

Love,
Sheri & The Boys

Happy 2024!
2023 was a wild one filled with change, many emotions surrounding those big life shifts and a deep appreciation for our community 💝

We are SO optimistic and ready for this new year, and can’t wait to surprise you with NEW cruise content and experiences! 

In 2023, our family went on 5 cruises with 4 cruise lines: 
🩵Seabourn to Alaska, Japan & Caribbean with Princess, Bermuda with NCL and Caribbean with Royal Caribbean. 
🩵We moved more than halfway across the country and bought a farmhouse that will keep us busy for at least 10 years! Hah! 
🩵We made the transition to full time entrepreneurship.

As we look forward to 2024, we’re deeply thankful for YOU. Every video you watch, podcast you listen to, comment you take the time to write, link you shop- it all matters and keeps us going! 

And, to our Patreon supporters, who have taken that support to the NEXT LEVEL to invest in us - it means a lot to our family 💝

Cheers to a healthy, content, and prosperous 2024.
Xoxo
Sheri & The Boys

Bye 2023, you were EPIC! 2024 is a blank slate…so ready for this adventure 🩵
